	<h2>Bonus tips for choosing the perfect band name</h2>
	<ol class="tips">
		<li><strong>Choose words that evoke strong visual imagery.</strong> If your band name paints an immediate image in someones brain, they'll be much more likely to remember you.</li>
		<li><strong>Combine words in unexpected ways.</strong> This is another great tactic to get your band embedded in your fans memory. When unusual things are mixed, it causes the brain to evaluate the combination. <a href="http://universosportinguista.blogspot.com/2009/09/surrealism-makes-you-smarter.html" target="_blank">[study on surrealism]</a></li>
		<li><strong>Be original.</strong> Don't be one of those bands that tries to make a name by hooking onto the identity of an existing famous band.</li>
		<li><strong>Drugs aren't the path to creativity.</strong> Anyone can be creative without the use of chemical stimulants. Expose yourself to new ideas, people and environments. Then be sure to continually write down your thoughts.</li>
		<li><strong>Be approachable.</strong> Think about your fans and how to connect with them. Let them help you create and explore. Maybe this line of thinking helps you with a band name but hopefully it's part of your overall messaging.</li>
